The man accused of killing the son of former Bophutatswana leader, Lucas Mangope is on Tuesday expected to appear in the Motswedi Magistrate s Court charges of murder. Gabonthone Mangope was killed on Saturday in Motswedi village where his father is a chief of Bahurutshe Boo- Manyane. Police say the deceased was stabbed to death with a knife in one of the streets of Motswedi. It is alleged that Mangope had an argument with the suspect before the stabbing occurred, although at this stage it is unclear what the argument was about. The motive of the killing is still unknown.